item.title: SpaceX, NASA to attempt second launch
item.description: Elon Musk's private rocket company SpaceX is set for a second attempt at launching two Americans into orbit from Florida for a mission that would mark the first spaceflight of NASA astronauts from US soil in nine years.

item.title: Lesotho’s ex-first lady on murder charge
item.description: Police are searching for Lesotho's former first lady who is accused of murder after a court revoked her bail.

item.title: Two dead after Sydney man stabs ex-partner
item.description: A Sydney woman has been stabbed to death by her former partner, who also died of stab wounds.

item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
Protests rock US over Floyd’s arrest death
item.description: Georgia's governor declared a state of emergency to activate the state National Guard as violence flared in Atlanta and in dozens of cities nationwide following the death in Minnesota of George Floyd after a white officer pressed a knee into his neck while taking him into custody.

item.title: Year 2 class isolates due to Melb cluster
item.description: A class of Year 2 students in Melbourne is in isolation for two weeks after a child tested positive for coronavirus.

item.title: Ruby Princess crew member has tuberculosis
item.description: A Ruby Princess crew member in a Sydney hospital has been diagnosed with tuberculosis, prompting authorities to notify all recent passengers.

item.title: Driver fails to stop after fatal WA crash
item.description: Two women have been killed in a crash in Perth's south, with the driver of the other car involved arrested after failing to stop.

item.title: ‘Lack of care’ for dead SA disabled woman
item.description: Disability rights advocates say the shocking death of a South Australian woman with cerebral palsy highlights a lack of community care for disabled people.

item.title: No new active virus cases from WA ship
item.description: No new active coronavirus cases have been detected in Western Australia but a historical case has been detected among the crew of the plagued Al Kuwait livestock ship.
